    "titleZh": "Data Analytics for IoT",
    "credits": 6,
    "recommendedYear": 2,
    "semester": "2",
    "courseType": "major_elective",
    "prerequisites": "COMP2118 or COMP2502 or MATH1013 or MATH1853 or MATH2014; and COMP2119",
    "exclusions": "None",
    "description": "This course introduces basic concepts, technologies, and applications of the Internet of Things (IoT), with a focus on data analytics. The course covers a range of enabling techniques in sensing, computing, analytics, learning for IoT and connects them to exciting applications in smart homes, healthcare, security, etc. The lectures cover the pipeline of data generation, data acquisition, data transportation, data analysis and learning, and data applications, with various topics from the fundamentals (e.g., signal processing, statistical analysis, machine learning) to real-world systems. Billions of things are connected today, and this course helps students to understand how IoT will evolve into AIoT (Artificial Intelligence of Things).",
    "sourceUrl": "https://www.cs.hku.hk/index.php/programmes/course-offered?infile=2025/comp3516.html",
